# Tenant Handling

- Some, not all, tables and data belong to a tenant
- Tenant context is accessible by using `src/Shared/Application/Service/TenantContextInterface.php`
- Unless explicit specified, non tenant context needs to be used and implemented.
- If specified, the persistence layer MUST use query builders extending `src/Shared/Infrastructure/Persistence/QueryBuilder.php`
- Queries for the public consumers MUST filter by the tenant
- Tenant handling SHOULD most of the time happen only in the infrastructure layer
- Domain aggregates MUST NOT be aware of the tenant unless specified by the user

## Tenant Aware Modules

The following modules must be fully tenant aware and MUST NOT expose their data to other tenants. By a module we mean a folder, a capability, in `src/Capability/<ModuleName>`

- Badges
- BusinessProcessModel
- BusinessRules
- DomainDocumentation
- OrganizationInvitations
- OrganizationInvoicing
- OrganizationSubscriptions
